TinyCC upstream pin
===================

Source:    https://github.com/TinyCC/tinycc
Submodule: vendor/tinycc/tinycc
Branch:    mob
Commit:    3b1fe97a596a7c69e693e962f4fe9b35128b68fd
License:   LGPL-2.1 (see vendor/tinycc/tinycc/COPYING; partial MIT
           relicensing consent recorded in vendor/tinycc/tinycc/RELICENSING)

The exact commit pinned above is the only revision SecureOS builds, audits,
and tests against. Bumping this pin requires a new vendor-bump PR that
re-runs the in-OS toolchain test suite and records any object-count or
total-size drift in the PR description (mirrors the BearSSL discipline,
issue #117).

This pin is the foundation of the in-OS toolchain effort
(plans/2026-05-28-in-os-toolchain-self-hosting.md). TinyCC is used because it
is a single, self-contained compiler that performs compile + assemble + link
in one process — SecureOS cannot spawn a separate assembler/linker.
